<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1244,1703]" pageId="5" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,441,1244,1271]" pageId="5" pageNumber="82">
Description of 
<typeStatus box="[332,437,1245,1271]" pageId="5" pageNumber="82">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
Size: 
<quantity box="[516,607,1244,1271]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="82" unit="mm" value="5.5">5.5 mm</quantity>
. Body dorsally green-black; eyes about as wide as vertex (dorsal view); frons golden-green; pronotum widest at anterior margin, anterior pronotal lobe absent; elytra without pubescent stripes, glabrous; elytral apices separately rounded with dentate margin; prosternal lobe large and arcuate on anterior margin; metasternal projection faintly impressed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1244,1703]" box="[199,914,1388,1415]" pageId="5" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,333,1388,1415]" pageId="5" pageNumber="82">Variability.</emphasis>
The species is known only from the male 
<typeStatus box="[808,910,1388,1414]" pageId="5" pageNumber="82">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="82" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1244,1703]" pageId="5" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,319,1424,1451]" pageId="5" pageNumber="82">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The species can be distinguished only by its very peculiar aedeagus. The medial lobe (penis) is robust, almost subtruncate on apex and twice as wide as the membranous sensory zones of the parameres (
<figureCitation box="[1232,1323,1460,1487]" captionStart="FIGURES 3" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1909,1934]" captionTargetBox="[157,1435,211,1874]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1435,211,1874]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 3A–3J. Dry preserved aedeagus of Agrilus. 3A, Agrilus acacivorus sp.nov.; 3B, A. albizivorus sp.nov.; 3C, A. aurigaster Jendek, 2011; 3D, A. babaulti Théry, 1930; 3E, A. coco sp.nov.; 3F, A. monadikos sp.nov.; 3G, A. occultus sp.nov.; 3H, A. presbys Jendek. 2011; 3I A. striatocollis Kerremans, 1892; 3J, A. terraereginae Blackburn, 1892." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3268309/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="82">Figs. 3F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1334,1371,1460,1487]" captionStart="FIGURES 5" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1893,1918]" captionTargetBox="[157,1425,216,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[151,1435,211,1874]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 5A–5I. Aedeagus of Agrilus mounted in DMHF. 5A–5C, 5E, 5I medial lobe (penis) exposed, 5D, 5F, 5H medial lobe (penis) in natural position. 5A, Agrilus acacivorus sp.nov.; 5B, A. albizivorus sp.nov.; 5C, A. babaulti Théry, 1930; 5D, A. monadikos sp.nov.; 5E, A. occultus sp.nov.; 5F, A. occultus sp.nov.; 5G, A. terraereginae Blackburn, 1892; 5H, A. viridicupreus Saunders, 1866; 5I, A. viridifrons Kerremans, 1893." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3268313/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="82">5D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
